TI  - Generalizable chiller model via domain-invariant representation learning: a real-life case study
AU  - Kim, J. H.
AU  - Jo, H. G.
AU  - Mun, J. Y.
AU  - Park, C. S.
PY  - 2026
T2  - Proceedings of the 2026 ASHRAE Winter Conference, January 31-February 4, 2026, Las Vegas, USA.
DO  - 10.63044/w26kimA07
UR  - https://store.accuristech.com/standards/a007-generalizable-chiller-model-via-domain-invariant-representation-learning-a-real-life-case-study?product_id=3066255
AB  - Data-driven models have faced a challenge of ensuring extrapolation ability to reduce their dependence on data. Although transfer learning can leverage knowledge from other domains, it may not fully capture dynamic characteristics of the target system because knowledge transfer is one-way. This study proposes a generalizable chiller modeling approach using domain-invariant representation learning for real-world chiller systems. Measured data from two heterogeneous chillers were collected over approximately four years. The domain-invariant model demonstrated superior performance for both accuracy and extrapolation ability through bidirectional data sharing across heterogeneous chillers.
