AB  - Data-driven models are easy to develop and can be accurate, but their performance can deteriorate on unseen and imbalanced datasets. This study proposes a Domain-Invariant Representation Learning (DIRL) chiller model that uses a bidirectional learning framework and shared hidden layers for two real-life chillers. Five modeling approaches were compared for accuracy and extrapolation ability. The DIRL model achieved the best extrapolation performance and maintained consistent predictive performance by learning general chiller knowledge from combined datasets through a shared feature extractor.
