AB  - This study compares five simulation models of real-life cooling towers in terms of accuracy, generalizability, and extrapolation ability: physics-based, data-driven, physics-informed hybrid, physics-guided hybrid, and transfer-learning hybrid models. Data were collected from the target cooling towers for approximately three years. The data-driven and hybrid models produced good predictive accuracy, while performance declined when models were transferred to a nearby identical system. Only the physics-based and transfer-learning hybrid models maintained physical consistency beyond the training data, and the transfer-learning hybrid performed best overall.
