TI  - Issues and Recommendations for Quasi Steady-State Building Energy Analysis: Focusing on a Domestic Building Energy Efficiency Rating Program (ECO2)
AU  - Lee, S. J.
AU  - Jo, H. G.
AU  - Yoo, Y. S.
AU  - Park, C. H.
AU  - Park, C. S.
PY  - 2024
JO  - Journal of the Architectural Institute of Korea, Vol. 40, No. 1, pp. 169-176.
DO  - 10.5659/JAIK.2024.40.1.169
UR  - https://www.dbpia.co.kr/journal/articleDetail?nodeId=NODE11698671
AB  - Building energy analysis can be categorized into steady-state, quasi-steady-state, and dynamic methods. Korean building energy standards rely on ECO2, which is based on a quasi-steady-state approach and accepts deterministic inputs and predefined usage profiles. This paper examines technical disadvantages of ECO2, including unrealistic geometry and HVAC modeling, non-adjustable default inputs, insufficient validation, lack of stochastic characteristics, and limited usefulness for energy-conscious decision making, and proposes recommendations for Korean building energy standards.
KW  - building energy standards
KW  - quasi steady-state
KW  - performance
