AB  - This paper presents predictive control of indoor PM2.5, PM10, and CO2 in a preschool classroom and an elementary-school gym using a lumped model, an artificial neural network, and a stochastic occupancy model. Models were trained with indoor and outdoor sensor data, ventilator status, and CCTV-derived occupancy. The neural-network controller achieved the highest rate of compliance with indoor-environment criteria in both spaces.
