AB  - This paper reports an optimal cooling control strategy for a makeup air unit in an existing building. A physics-based simulation model predicts supply-air temperature and humidity after two cooling coils as well as chiller cooling-energy consumption. The model is used to determine energy-efficient operation while satisfying the required supply-air conditions.
