AB  - This study suggests a real-time indoor daylight simulation method using minimal data from two reference sensors and two prior measurements at target points. The minimal data substitutes for components in the daylight coefficient equation. The approach was validated with seven days of on-site measurements, achieving a 7.3% mean absolute percentage error and a 0.3% normalized mean bias error.
