AU  - Jo, H. G.
AU  - Kim, Y. S.
AU  - Park, C. S.
PY  - 2021
T2  - Proceedings of the 2021 Winter Simulation Conference, December 13-17, 2021, Phoenix, Arizona, USA.
UR  - https://www.informs-sim.org/wsc21papers/052.pdf
AB  - This commercial case study presents a data-driven daylight simulation model for a factory building. Using solar altitude, solar azimuth, cloud cover, and illuminance measured at a single reference point, a Gaussian process model predicts illuminance at multiple indoor points. The model achieved an average coefficient of variation of root mean square error of 20.4% and was integrated with continuous dimming control.
