DO  - 10.5659/JAIK.2021.37.12.255
UR  - https://www.dbpia.co.kr/journal/articleDetail?nodeId=NODE10819108
AB  - Development of a stochastic daylighting prediction model for a large open-space building is presented. The model uses solar altitude and azimuth, illuminance at a reference point, and cloud cover to predict daylight illuminance at sixteen workplane points. Gaussian process modeling captures the stochastic characteristics of the indoor daylight environment. The model was integrated with electric-lighting control, and eight days of validation indicated an energy saving of 12.3%.
